21 44-3-260.
22 As used in this article, the term:
23 (1) 'Affiliate' means any entity that directly or indirectly owns or controls, is owned or
24 controlled by, or is under any other common ownership or control with a business
25 enterprise.
26 (2) 'Business enterprise' means any corporation, association, partnership, limited liability
27 company, limited partnership, trust, issuer, or other private legal entity organized under
28 the laws of this state, the United States, the District of Columbia, or any other state,
29 territory, or dependency of the United States or under the laws of a foreign country.
30 (3) 'Claimant' means an aggrieved person who seeks recovery of damages under this
31 article; provided, however, such term shall not include a government entity or any officer
32 or employee of a government entity acting in his or her official capacity.
33 (4) 'Government entity' means any office, agency, authority, department, commission,
34 board, body, division, instrumentality, or institution of the executive, legislative, or
35 judicial branch of the state government or of any political subdivision within this state.
36 (5) 'Multifamily residence' means a parcel of real property that has upon it a structure
37 that contains four or more individual dwelling units, each of which is designed
38 exclusively for use and occupation by one family.
39 (6) 'Residential property' means a single-family residence or a multifamily residence,
40 including all improvements thereon.
41 (7) 'Single-family residence' means a parcel of real property that has upon it a:
